### Step 2: Fix the Database (Permissions)

Once you redeploy the code above, the error message will likely say:
> *"new row violates row-level security policy for table 'orders'"*

This means Supabase is protecting the table. You need to unlock it.

1.  Go to **Supabase.com** -> **SQL Editor**.
2.  **Paste and Run this script** to fix the permissions for everything:

```sql
-- 1. DISABLE RLS (Easiest way for now)
alter table orders disable row level security;
alter table menu_items disable row level security;
alter table toppings disable row level security;
alter table customers disable row level security;
alter table expenses disable row level security;
alter table store_settings disable row level security;

-- 2. UPDATE COLUMNS (Just in case they are missing)
-- This adds missing columns without deleting data
alter table orders add column if not exists source text;
alter table orders add column if not exists net_amount numeric;
alter table orders add column if not exists delivery_zone text;
alter table orders add column if not exists pickup_time text;

-- 3. VERIFY
select 'Setup Complete' as status;
```

**After running this SQL script, try to order again on your phone.** It should work immediately! 🍕

Great news! **You do NOT need to change any code.**

Because I updated the app to use "Environment Variables" (Variables that live outside the code), this app is now **"Project Agnostic"**. It doesn't care if the project is named "Pizza Damac" or "oat299-sudo". It only cares about the **Keys** you give it in Netlify.

### 🚀 How to switch to "oat299-sudo's Project":

You only need to do **2 steps** (No coding required):

#### Step 1: Update Netlify Keys
Since you have a new Supabase project, you have **New Keys**. The old keys will not work.

1.  Log in to **Supabase** -> Go to **"oat299-sudo's Project"**.
2.  Go to **Settings (Gear Icon)** -> **API**.
3.  Copy the **Project URL**.
4.  Copy the **Anon Public Key**.
5.  Go to **Netlify** -> **Site Settings** -> **Environment variables**.
6.  **Update** `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` with the new URL.
7.  **Update** `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` with the new Key.
8.  **Re-deploy** your site (Deploys -> Trigger deploy -> Clear cache and deploy).

#### Step 2: Initialize the Database (Critical)
Since "oat299-sudo's Project" is a *new* project, **its database is empty**. It doesn't have the "Menu", "Orders", or "Customers" tables yet. The app will look broken (empty menu) until you run the script.

1.  In Supabase (**oat299-sudo's Project**), go to **SQL Editor**.
2.  Click **New Query**.
3.  **Paste and Run** this Master Script to create all the tables for your new project:

```sql
-- 1. Create Tables
create table if not exists menu_items (
  id text primary key,
  name text, name_th text, description text, description_th text,
  base_price numeric, image text, available boolean default true, category text,
  is_best_seller boolean default false, combo_count numeric default 0
);
create table if not exists toppings (id text primary key, name text, name_th text, price numeric);
create table if not exists orders (
  id text primary key, customer_name text, customer_phone text, type text, source text,
  status text, total_amount numeric, net_amount numeric, created_at timestamptz default now(),
  note text, delivery_address text, delivery_zone text, delivery_fee numeric,
  payment_method text, pickup_time text, table_number text, items jsonb
);
create table if not exists customers (
  phone text primary key, name text, address text, birthday text, password text,
  loyalty_points numeric default 0, tier text default 'Bronze',
  saved_favorites jsonb, order_history jsonb, pdpa_accepted boolean, saved_addresses jsonb
);
create table if not exists expenses (id text primary key, description text, amount numeric, category text, date timestamptz, note text);
create table if not exists store_settings (
  id text primary key, is_open boolean default true, closed_message text default '',
  promo_banner_url text, promo_content_type text, holiday_start text, holiday_end text
);

-- 2. Unlock Permissions (Disable RLS)
alter table menu_items disable row level security;
alter table toppings disable row level security;
alter table orders disable row level security;
alter table customers disable row level security;
alter table expenses disable row level security;
alter table store_settings disable row level security;

-- 3. Turn on Realtime
alter publication supabase_realtime add table orders;
alter publication supabase_realtime add table menu_items;
alter publication supabase_realtime add table store_settings;

-- 4. Fill Menu (So it's not empty)
insert into menu_items (id, name, name_th, description, description_th, base_price, category, image, available, is_best_seller, combo_count) values
('promo1', 'Family Combo Set', 'ชุดครอบครัวสุดคุ้ม', '2 Large Pizzas + Sides', 'พิซซ่าถาดใหญ่ 2 ถาด + ของทานเล่น', 899, 'promotion', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1565299624946-b28f40a0ae38?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80', true, true, 2),
('p1', 'Pizza Damac', 'พิซซ่า ดาแมค (แนะนำ)', 'Signature toppings.', 'พิซซ่าซิกเนเจอร์', 380, 'pizza', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1604382354936-07c5d9983bd3?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80', true, true, 0),
('p4', 'Pizza Pepperoni', 'พิซซ่า เปปเปอโรนี', 'Spicy pepperoni.', 'เปปเปอโรนีรสเผ็ด', 380, 'pizza', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1628840042765-356cda07504e?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80', true, true, 0),
('s1', 'Garlic Bread', 'ขนมปังกระเทียม', 'Crispy garlic bread.', 'ขนมปังกระเทียมกรอบ', 120, 'appetizer', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1619535860434-7f0863384d41?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80', true, false, 0),
('d1', 'Cola', 'โค้ก', 'Refreshing.', 'เย็นซ่า', 40, 'drink', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1622483767028-3f66f32aef97?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80', true, false, 0);

insert into toppings (id, name, name_th, price) values
('t1', 'Extra Cheese', 'เพิ่มชีส', 50), ('t2', 'Mushrooms', 'เห็ด', 30), ('t5', 'Bacon', 'เบคอน', 40), ('t8', 'Pepperoni', 'เปปเปอโรนี', 50);

insert into store_settings (id, is_open) values ('global', true) on conflict do nothing;
```

**Once you do these 2 steps, your site will be fully live on the new database!** 🍕
